1
00:00:56,078 --> 00:00:58,914
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:01,959 --> 00:01:02,960
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

3
00:01:03,043 --> 00:01:04,170
Joo In-a's

4
00:01:05,087 --> 00:01:06,130
having an affair?

5
00:01:09,758 --> 00:01:11,844
HEAD OF AUDIT JOO IN-A

6
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,138
Will you hear me out?

7
00:01:14,221 --> 00:01:16,557
It's really a misunderstanding,
Ms. Joo.

8
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:18,767
I said no, but the supplier said

9
00:01:19,268 --> 00:01:20,686
it's customary.

10
00:01:21,228 --> 00:01:23,689
Ms. Joo... Come on, Ms. Joo.

11
00:01:24,482 --> 00:01:26,317
Please, listen to me.

12
00:01:27,610 --> 00:01:28,694
Let me off just this once.

13
00:01:29,778 --> 00:01:32,281
My kids are young, and my wife
quit her job to care for them.

14
00:01:32,364 --> 00:01:34,158
I'm all they have right now.

15
00:01:34,909 --> 00:01:36,202
Please, just this one time.

16
00:01:37,912 --> 00:01:40,664
You should've thought of your wife
and kids before taking the kickback.

17
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,875
Don't use them
as a sentimental excuse.

18
00:01:43,167 --> 00:01:44,210
What was that?

19
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,921
Hey, you.

20
00:02:02,645 --> 00:02:03,979
Know your limits.

21
00:02:04,563 --> 00:02:07,066
A cornered mouse can bite the cat.

22
00:02:17,326 --> 00:02:18,327
Darn it!

23
00:02:25,584 --> 00:02:26,835
What are you staring at?

24
00:02:29,296 --> 00:02:31,465
You weren't hoping
I'd get slapped, were you?

25
00:02:43,143 --> 00:02:44,520
She's such a freak.

26
00:02:49,108 --> 00:02:50,651
Joo In-a couldn't possibly be
having an affair.

27
00:02:51,277 --> 00:02:53,362
- It can't be.
- Mr. Noh.

28
00:02:57,741 --> 00:02:58,742
Yes?

29
00:03:02,454 --> 00:03:03,956
I thought you wanted to talk to me.

30
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:06,292
Oh, well...

31
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:07,710
All right, for now...

32
00:03:08,544 --> 00:03:11,505
Let's backtrack strategically
until I've grasped the situation.

33
00:03:13,549 --> 00:03:14,883
I wanted to apologize.

34
00:03:16,218 --> 00:03:18,220
I was rude at karaoke yesterday.

35
00:03:19,930 --> 00:03:21,682
I'm really sorry, Ms. Joo.

36
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:29,023
I get it.

37
00:03:29,898 --> 00:03:32,151
I was a bit indifferent
and insensitive.

38
00:03:32,526 --> 00:03:35,279
I put someone like you
in charge of very limited duties.

39
00:03:35,946 --> 00:03:36,989
You must've been frustrated.

40
00:03:38,616 --> 00:03:39,617
Well...

41
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:43,579
I'll give you more work.

42
00:03:44,872 --> 00:03:45,914
Sure.

43
00:04:00,888 --> 00:04:02,389
Wait, Mr. Noh.

44
00:04:03,015 --> 00:04:04,224
Why are you doing this?

45
00:04:07,102 --> 00:04:08,145
Oh, dear.

46
00:04:08,604 --> 00:04:10,522
Why did you have to go and...

47
00:04:11,565 --> 00:04:13,317
Why did you take her on?

48
00:04:15,986 --> 00:04:18,072
You really need to be careful.

49
00:04:18,155 --> 00:04:19,573
Seeing how she handled Mr. Seo

50
00:04:19,657 --> 00:04:21,492
made me realize
how she got called "JJCC."

51
00:04:21,992 --> 00:04:24,828
"Jeer Joo, Chaos Comes."

52
00:04:24,912 --> 00:04:26,872
That spells JJCC.

53
00:04:26,955 --> 00:04:28,415
JEER JOO, CHAOS COMES

54
00:04:28,499 --> 00:04:30,292
Gosh, just thinking about it...

55
00:04:31,835 --> 00:04:32,920
Mr. Noh.

56
00:04:34,505 --> 00:04:35,673
I'll leave this here.

57
00:04:35,923 --> 00:04:37,216
Since you're at it.

58
00:04:37,299 --> 00:04:39,385
You know I'm rooting for you, right?

59
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,803
Stay strong.

60
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,143
Jeez...

61
00:05:09,456 --> 00:05:10,541
My gosh.

62
00:05:34,314 --> 00:05:36,734
What the heck?

63
00:05:37,609 --> 00:05:39,236
Darn it all.

64
00:05:47,536 --> 00:05:49,288
JJCC, my foot.

65
00:05:50,372 --> 00:05:53,125
She's just an employee
like everyone else.

66
00:05:54,585 --> 00:05:56,003
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

67
00:05:56,086 --> 00:05:57,337
MS. JOO IN-A IS INVOLVED

68
00:05:57,421 --> 00:05:58,881
IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

69
00:06:00,841 --> 00:06:02,092
Yes.

70
00:06:02,176 --> 00:06:05,220
If that report turns out to be true

71
00:06:06,054 --> 00:06:08,640
that means I'll have what I need
to take Joo In-a down.

72
00:06:10,058 --> 00:06:11,143
This could be

73
00:06:12,227 --> 00:06:13,896
my opportunity.

74
00:06:16,148 --> 00:06:17,566
Fine, Joo In-a.

75
00:06:18,484 --> 00:06:19,777
I'll take you on.

76
00:06:20,944 --> 00:06:23,363
Let's see who comes to a grizzly end.

77
00:06:37,169 --> 00:06:40,005
EPISODE 3:
A WOMAN WITH A TWIST

78
00:06:45,135 --> 00:06:46,220
A workplace is a battlefield.

79
00:06:47,679 --> 00:06:50,516
Every single day,
we fight hard to survive and win.

80
00:06:53,101 --> 00:06:54,686
The fundamental rule of war is IFF.

81
00:06:56,021 --> 00:06:57,564
Identifying friend or foe.

82
00:07:00,234 --> 00:07:01,235
However...

83
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,153
Good morning.

84
00:07:03,737 --> 00:07:05,697
Ma'am, you colored your hair.

85
00:07:06,114 --> 00:07:07,741
You look 20 years younger.

86
00:07:07,991 --> 00:07:08,992
Hello.

87
00:07:09,701 --> 00:07:12,788
Sang-hyeon, you drank too much.
Soothe yourself or you'll get sick.

88
00:07:12,871 --> 00:07:15,207
Identifying friend and foe at work

89
00:07:15,707 --> 00:07:16,750
is not at all easy.

90
00:07:18,043 --> 00:07:19,962
Some foes look like friends.

91
00:07:20,337 --> 00:07:21,797
I never see you around.

92
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,131
We should meet up soon.

93
00:07:23,549 --> 00:07:26,093
Your team and mine
could exchange info.

94
00:07:26,385 --> 00:07:28,095
Yes, sure. That would be nice.

95
00:07:28,262 --> 00:07:31,014
Let's meet for a drink another time.

96
00:07:31,098 --> 00:07:32,099
Sounds good.

97
00:07:32,975 --> 00:07:34,142
Yes, take care.

98
00:07:36,311 --> 00:07:38,522
- Oh, my gosh.
- Today's friend

99
00:07:39,189 --> 00:07:40,399
could become tomorrow's foe.

100
00:07:40,482 --> 00:07:42,192
Why are you pushing this on your own?

101
00:07:42,276 --> 00:07:43,485
You just clocked in?

102
00:07:43,569 --> 00:07:45,737
I do this every day.

103
00:07:45,821 --> 00:07:46,947
Even so.

104
00:07:47,030 --> 00:07:48,949
Be careful. You might hurt your back.

105
00:07:49,032 --> 00:07:50,784
Don't you worry about my back.

106
00:07:51,285 --> 00:07:53,745
Pushing this cart takes know-how,
not brute strength.

107
00:07:53,829 --> 00:07:55,622
- You do this.
- Oh, my gosh.

108
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:59,418
This is almost scientific.

109
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:02,045
It's nice to have some help.

110
00:08:03,422 --> 00:08:06,925
TEAM LEADER MOO KWANG-IL

111
00:08:12,139 --> 00:08:13,390
But one thing is clear.

112
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,226
The moment you identify a foe

113
00:08:17,019 --> 00:08:18,604
that is exactly what they become.

114
00:08:29,823 --> 00:08:30,824
As of now

115
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:33,201
I will sharpen my blade quietly

116
00:08:34,077 --> 00:08:35,203
for my archenemy.

117
00:08:35,287 --> 00:08:36,455
NEW FOLDER: NONAME

118
00:08:36,538 --> 00:08:39,416
And plan a critical blow to Joo In-a.

119
00:08:42,294 --> 00:08:43,754
Ms. Joo In-a.

120
00:08:44,588 --> 00:08:47,925
You asked to be excluded
from the executive staff meeting.

121
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:51,094
Yes, Haemu's Audit Team
is an audit team only in name.

122
00:08:51,178 --> 00:08:52,930
Our tasks are not independent.

123
00:08:53,305 --> 00:08:55,057
We need to renew
our chain of command.

124
00:08:55,474 --> 00:08:58,143
We are fully under the control
of management for now.

125
00:08:59,478 --> 00:09:01,146
That almost hurts to hear.

126
00:09:02,522 --> 00:09:03,941
I can't approve your request.

127
00:09:04,983 --> 00:09:06,318
I would like for you

128
00:09:07,694 --> 00:09:08,987
to be under my control.

129
00:09:13,325 --> 00:09:15,035
Please reconsider my request.

130
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:18,121
Well, I have a lot of work
to catch up on.

131
00:09:18,205 --> 00:09:19,539
I will excuse myself.

132
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,467
She's as independent
as she needs to be.

133
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:32,052
Shall I hear from HR next?

134
00:09:35,847 --> 00:09:37,516
Okay, so...

135
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,309
President Jeon wants to reinstate

136
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:43,021
Managing Director Jeon Sung-yeol
to the head office.

137
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:46,400
He called me himself this morning.

138
00:09:46,483 --> 00:09:48,527
Yes, I'm aware of that.

139
00:09:50,112 --> 00:09:51,154
You are, right?

140
00:09:51,655 --> 00:09:54,157
I knew you'd be aware
of the situation.

141
00:09:54,241 --> 00:09:55,867
You are the vice president.

142
00:09:56,326 --> 00:10:00,163
Still, you should've run it by me
before bringing this to the meeting.

143
00:10:00,497 --> 00:10:01,498
It's a sensitive matter.

144
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:04,876
I apologize. That was careless of me.

145
00:10:06,586 --> 00:10:07,963
To be honest, personally

146
00:10:08,964 --> 00:10:11,216
the risk of reinstating
Managing Director Jeon

147
00:10:11,508 --> 00:10:13,969
right after the end
of his probation period

148
00:10:14,553 --> 00:10:16,179
is quite concerning.

149
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,562
Is it the President?

150
00:10:29,526 --> 00:10:30,736
PRESIDENT JEON

151
00:10:37,701 --> 00:10:39,286
Hello, Father. It's Jae-yeol.

152
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:41,538
Did I call the wrong person?

153
00:10:41,621 --> 00:10:44,666
I apologize. We were in a meeting,
so I answered her phone.

154
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:46,084
Sign the form.

155
00:10:47,210 --> 00:10:48,253
The thing is...

156
00:10:51,048 --> 00:10:52,507
HR voiced their concern.

157
00:10:53,508 --> 00:10:55,260
It's still a bit early.

158
00:10:55,343 --> 00:10:57,179
Some will criticize us
for putting on a show...

159
00:10:57,262 --> 00:10:58,722
Haven't you seen
Haemu Construction's stocks?

160
00:10:58,972 --> 00:11:00,182
You must acknowledge what's due.

161
00:11:00,766 --> 00:11:01,850
Don't make me repeat myself.

162
00:11:18,408 --> 00:11:21,119
Thanks for working hard today.
See you tomorrow.

163
00:11:21,203 --> 00:11:22,996
- Goodbye.
- Take care.

164
00:11:25,290 --> 00:11:26,666
Who wants to have dinner with me?

165
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,418
My wife wants me to eat out.

166
00:11:30,754 --> 00:11:31,755
No one?

167
00:11:32,464 --> 00:11:34,132
- See you tomorrow.
- Yes, bye.

168
00:11:34,216 --> 00:11:35,467
- Goodbye.
- There's no one.

169
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,761
Are you all trying to lose weight?

170
00:11:38,178 --> 00:11:41,014
Yes, sure. Got it.

171
00:11:57,906 --> 00:11:58,907
RECORDING, REFRAIN FROM TOUCHING

172
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:01,785
Project No Name,
following the target.

173
00:12:35,068 --> 00:12:36,820
Is she going straight home?

174
00:13:27,954 --> 00:13:30,457
One triangle gimbap, a can of beer

175
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,210
and a box of digestive medicine?

176
00:13:38,882 --> 00:13:40,217
My gosh.

177
00:13:43,428 --> 00:13:44,554
What are you, mister?

178
00:13:44,804 --> 00:13:46,765
Are you a stalker? A beggar?

179
00:13:50,894 --> 00:13:51,937
Did you hear the news?

180
00:13:52,187 --> 00:13:54,147
The VP's stepbrother
Managing Director Jeon Sung-yeol

181
00:13:54,231 --> 00:13:55,523
is coming back here.

182
00:13:56,107 --> 00:13:59,402
They say the president
favors him over the VP.

183
00:14:00,278 --> 00:14:02,781
Is it because
he's the current wife's son?

184
00:14:02,864 --> 00:14:04,199
This is top secret.

185
00:14:04,282 --> 00:14:06,201
The VP's birth mother.

186
00:14:06,451 --> 00:14:09,204
She was basically thrown out
because of a mental illness.

187
00:14:09,412 --> 00:14:11,414
They called her
a disgrace to the family.

188
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:15,585
There's even talk
that they think it's hereditary.

189
00:14:15,669 --> 00:14:17,379
- Then the VP...
- Come on, now.

190
00:14:17,712 --> 00:14:20,632
Aren't you two too young
to have a prejudice like that?

191
00:14:21,675 --> 00:14:24,469
If Director Jeon does come back

192
00:14:24,552 --> 00:14:27,722
all we have to do
is decide whose side to take.

193
00:14:28,139 --> 00:14:29,349
Wouldn't it be better

194
00:14:29,849 --> 00:14:32,560
to side with the managing director?

195
00:14:33,019 --> 00:14:36,356
The current VP is in charge
only in title.

196
00:14:36,439 --> 00:14:37,607
He doesn't have a stake in Haemu.

197
00:14:39,401 --> 00:14:40,443
Hey, guys.

198
00:14:41,736 --> 00:14:42,779
It's not like that.

199
00:14:43,697 --> 00:14:45,115
You never know.

200
00:14:45,198 --> 00:14:47,993
The VP has an influential wife.

201
00:14:48,785 --> 00:14:50,787
His father-in-law owns Sesan Group.

202
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:53,581
The President arranged that marriage
because he needed something.

203
00:14:53,665 --> 00:14:55,292
He has to be wary of them.

204
00:14:55,375 --> 00:14:56,459
You're right.

205
00:14:56,543 --> 00:14:58,336
Then we really don't know
what'll happen.

206
00:14:58,420 --> 00:14:59,629
What I can say for sure is

207
00:14:59,713 --> 00:15:03,591
our company is about to see
the biggest storm in history.

208
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:05,343
You should be careful.

209
00:15:10,932 --> 00:15:12,392
- Hey, Mr. Moo.
- What?

210
00:15:13,059 --> 00:15:14,811
- Come see me.
- What for?

211
00:15:14,894 --> 00:15:16,479
- Follow me.
- Why?

212
00:15:18,315 --> 00:15:20,025
I packed this for you.

213
00:15:20,108 --> 00:15:22,027
- What is this?
- We made them

214
00:15:22,277 --> 00:15:25,030
for the executives,
and there were a lot of leftovers.

215
00:15:25,697 --> 00:15:27,782
Your wife is looking after twins.

216
00:15:28,074 --> 00:15:30,201
She won't have the time
to cook for herself.

217
00:15:30,285 --> 00:15:31,619
Take some home for her.

218
00:15:32,370 --> 00:15:35,623
Gosh, she's going to taste
some fancy food, thanks to you.

219
00:15:36,624 --> 00:15:37,751
My word.

220
00:15:37,959 --> 00:15:39,544
There's one more thing.

221
00:15:39,627 --> 00:15:41,713
It's not much.
Buy your kids some clothes.

222
00:15:41,796 --> 00:15:43,298
My kids have enough clothes.

223
00:15:43,381 --> 00:15:45,342
You gave too much money

224
00:15:45,425 --> 00:15:47,844
when you attended
my father's funeral.

225
00:15:48,219 --> 00:15:50,138
I didn't get to thank you then.
Take the money.

226
00:15:50,221 --> 00:15:51,723
- It's fine. It wasn't much.
- No.

227
00:15:51,806 --> 00:15:53,433
- You don't need to.
- Take it.

228
00:15:53,516 --> 00:15:54,893
- I don't want it.
- Don't say no.

229
00:15:54,976 --> 00:15:56,603
- You need to stop, ma'am.
- Take it.

230
00:15:56,686 --> 00:15:57,937
Don't do that.

231
00:15:58,563 --> 00:15:59,647
- No.
- What's this?

232
00:16:00,023 --> 00:16:01,483
Can you not do this?

233
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,486
What kind of scene is this?

234
00:16:08,365 --> 00:16:09,491
This is insane.

235
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:11,117
What are they doing out here?

236
00:16:36,059 --> 00:16:38,186
A triangle gimbap and a can of beer.

237
00:16:38,853 --> 00:16:40,438
That's all she buys every time?

238
00:16:40,897 --> 00:16:43,691
Yes, I thought the lady

239
00:16:43,775 --> 00:16:45,026
just had a small appetite.

240
00:16:45,485 --> 00:16:46,903
I see.

241
00:16:50,156 --> 00:16:52,200
Does she not like eating?

242
00:16:55,537 --> 00:16:56,788
Did she ever

243
00:16:57,872 --> 00:16:59,499
come here with a man?

244
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,961
No, I never even saw her
with a woman.

245
00:17:03,044 --> 00:17:05,088
- She's always on her own.
- Is she?

246
00:17:08,216 --> 00:17:11,094
You must be really smart, Rhena.

247
00:17:11,177 --> 00:17:12,554
You remember all the customers.

248
00:17:12,637 --> 00:17:14,848
No, I only remember because it's her.

249
00:17:14,931 --> 00:17:16,724
Because it's her? How come?

250
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,351
She's pretty.

251
00:17:18,435 --> 00:17:20,854
What? She's pretty?
Joo... That woman?

252
00:17:20,937 --> 00:17:21,980
Yes.

253
00:17:32,449 --> 00:17:33,658
Well, I guess.

254
00:17:33,741 --> 00:17:35,702
We all have
different beauty standards.

255
00:17:36,077 --> 00:17:39,289
She must be what you consider pretty.

256
00:17:44,669 --> 00:17:47,172
Hey, do you want another ice cream?

257
00:17:47,714 --> 00:17:49,048
No, buy me wine.

258
00:17:52,802 --> 00:17:54,888
- Rhena, I drove...
- To share with my boyfriend.

259
00:17:59,476 --> 00:18:01,603
Where would the princesses
like to go?

260
00:18:03,188 --> 00:18:04,314
Where shall we go?

261
00:18:04,731 --> 00:18:06,357
- That way.
- That way?

262
00:18:06,441 --> 00:18:07,901
Here we go.

263
00:18:10,028 --> 00:18:11,362
We've reached the ocean.

264
00:18:11,446 --> 00:18:12,447
Where do we go now?

265
00:18:13,364 --> 00:18:14,365
Backward?

266
00:18:19,037 --> 00:18:20,622
Where shall we go now? Which way?

267
00:18:21,372 --> 00:18:22,832
- This way?
- Girls.

268
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:25,293
It's past your bedtime.

269
00:18:25,376 --> 00:18:27,128
Go and brush your teeth.

270
00:18:27,212 --> 00:18:29,130
Mommy Monster's angry. Get away.

271
00:18:29,506 --> 00:18:31,049
Run away.

272
00:18:32,008 --> 00:18:33,426
Gosh. I feel so hot.

273
00:18:33,843 --> 00:18:37,347
Oh, dear. It's hard work
raising young kids at my age.

274
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:38,765
Save your energy.

275
00:18:39,182 --> 00:18:41,351
You need to work
until they finish university.

276
00:18:41,434 --> 00:18:42,519
Oh, my gosh.

277
00:18:43,144 --> 00:18:44,938
Oh, dear. My poor knees.

278
00:18:46,814 --> 00:18:48,066
- Honey.
- Yes?

279
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:51,110
Your cafeteria food is delicious.

280
00:18:51,194 --> 00:18:52,362
Large companies are the best.

281
00:18:52,445 --> 00:18:53,738
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

282
00:18:54,155 --> 00:18:56,032
It tastes even better
because someone else made it.

283
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:58,493
Take your time.

284
00:18:58,576 --> 00:18:59,827
Can you bring food home
every now and then?

285
00:19:00,954 --> 00:19:02,080
I'll do that.

286
00:19:04,165 --> 00:19:05,625
It's great to see you enjoy it.

287
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,001
Here's some water.

288
00:19:14,425 --> 00:19:15,468
You're home.

289
00:19:16,177 --> 00:19:18,721
You're late. Did you meet someone?

290
00:19:20,098 --> 00:19:21,182
No, I worked late.

291
00:19:26,187 --> 00:19:28,231
Why did you spend so much
at a convenience store?

292
00:19:28,314 --> 00:19:29,357
Oh, that?

293
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:32,026
The part-timer
bullied me into paying.

294
00:19:33,319 --> 00:19:34,320
Gosh.

295
00:19:34,779 --> 00:19:36,531
Gosh, ten condoms?

296
00:19:37,198 --> 00:19:38,283
What?

297
00:19:42,161 --> 00:19:43,663
Jeez, that kid...

298
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,373
I wonder if her parents know

299
00:19:45,665 --> 00:19:47,041
what she's up to instead of studying.

300
00:19:48,251 --> 00:19:51,129
If they heard, they'd be relieved
that she knows enough

301
00:19:51,212 --> 00:19:52,672
to take precautions.

302
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:56,050
They must be really in love
if they need ten boxes.

303
00:19:58,344 --> 00:20:00,722
Hey, ten boxes is nothing.

304
00:20:01,639 --> 00:20:04,183
You know... Back in my day...

305
00:20:15,403 --> 00:20:17,697
Is that what you're eating
for dinner?

306
00:20:17,989 --> 00:20:19,073
Why didn't you order takeout?

307
00:20:19,157 --> 00:20:21,576
I had dinner.
This is a late-night snack.

308
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:25,705
Do you want one?
It was buy one, get one free.

309
00:20:33,921 --> 00:20:36,299
KIMCHI AND SPICY PORK TRIANGLE GIMBAP

310
00:20:36,924 --> 00:20:37,925
Hey.

311
00:20:39,677 --> 00:20:41,220
I know someone

312
00:20:41,304 --> 00:20:43,806
who eats just one triangle gimbap
for dinner every day.

313
00:20:46,059 --> 00:20:47,477
What kind of person would do that?

314
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:49,145
They must be poor.

315
00:20:49,228 --> 00:20:50,438
No, it's not that.

316
00:20:51,648 --> 00:20:53,024
They make a decent amount.

317
00:20:55,485 --> 00:20:56,486
Then maybe

318
00:20:58,112 --> 00:20:59,614
they just eat to survive.

319
00:21:00,073 --> 00:21:03,034
Some people eat the bare minimum
so they don't die.

320
00:21:03,993 --> 00:21:05,870
They might look like they have a lot

321
00:21:06,704 --> 00:21:08,581
but they feel empty inside.

322
00:21:09,582 --> 00:21:10,583
That's why

323
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:13,002
they don't feel full
even though they eat.

324
00:21:13,711 --> 00:21:15,963
They don't feel energized
even though they sleep.

325
00:21:22,303 --> 00:21:23,471
Who are you talking about?

326
00:21:24,222 --> 00:21:26,683
It can't be you, seeing you're eating
a late-night snack.

327
00:21:32,105 --> 00:21:33,981
- Hey, Seung-hee.
- A-jeong.

328
00:21:34,273 --> 00:21:36,067
Sorry for calling late at night.

329
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:37,777
Did you check out
the anonymous bulletin board?

330
00:21:38,069 --> 00:21:40,738
There are endless posts
about the VP and his stepbrother.

331
00:21:42,532 --> 00:21:44,283
GET SOME POPCORN READY
SO DO THEY HAVE DIFFERENT MOMS?

332
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:46,369
A LEGENDARY SITUATION AT HAEMU
GOODBYE TO J'S SUPPORTERS

333
00:21:49,664 --> 00:21:51,207
Information Team!

334
00:21:51,290 --> 00:21:53,459
Do something about it!

335
00:21:53,710 --> 00:21:56,212
Take down the posts
as soon as they come up.

336
00:21:56,504 --> 00:21:58,089
Or block certain keywords.

337
00:21:58,172 --> 00:22:00,091
Can't you block posts
that say "birth mom"?

338
00:22:00,174 --> 00:22:02,427
That won't stop people
from using other terms.

339
00:22:03,344 --> 00:22:05,138
If we block every post on this topic

340
00:22:05,221 --> 00:22:08,224
they'll complain that HR
is censoring public opinion.

341
00:22:08,725 --> 00:22:12,103
And work.com
can't be controlled or censored.

342
00:22:13,813 --> 00:22:15,064
Be reasonable.

343
00:22:15,857 --> 00:22:17,191
I'm not asking you
to censor anything.

344
00:22:18,568 --> 00:22:19,861
That can't be the only solution.

345
00:22:22,029 --> 00:22:24,282
We each have just one mouth.

346
00:22:25,408 --> 00:22:26,576
Can't you

347
00:22:27,201 --> 00:22:28,870
come up with an idea?

348
00:22:34,125 --> 00:22:35,543
This is driving me insane.

349
00:22:37,128 --> 00:22:38,880
- Sir.
- What?

350
00:22:39,464 --> 00:22:40,631
Can you take a look at this?

351
00:22:40,923 --> 00:22:41,966
What is it?

352
00:22:43,009 --> 00:22:44,719
Someone posted it yesterday.

353
00:22:46,387 --> 00:22:48,097
How about we use this
to our advantage?

354
00:22:48,723 --> 00:22:50,224
It could gain some interest.

355
00:22:50,808 --> 00:22:52,059
"Middle-aged romance"?

356
00:22:52,769 --> 00:22:53,770
Hang on.

357
00:22:54,395 --> 00:22:57,523
I know this jawline from somewhere.

358
00:22:59,358 --> 00:23:00,443
Team Leader Moo?

359
00:23:00,735 --> 00:23:02,028
Hey, Moo...

360
00:23:03,362 --> 00:23:05,573
Good find, Ms. Oh. Can you move over?

361
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:08,367
Yes, let's put this to good use.

362
00:23:09,076 --> 00:23:12,079
Let's see.
A middle-aged woman. Madam...

363
00:23:12,288 --> 00:23:13,706
How does "Madam Killer" sound?

364
00:23:13,998 --> 00:23:15,166
Well...

365
00:23:15,583 --> 00:23:16,918
- That's a bit...
- Then...

366
00:23:17,794 --> 00:23:20,171
"An audit team leader's affair."

367
00:23:20,505 --> 00:23:21,631
Is that more provocative?

368
00:23:21,714 --> 00:23:24,050
Isn't it a bit much
to reveal his identity?

369
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:26,511
Revealing his identity
will increase the impact.

370
00:23:27,428 --> 00:23:29,472
You don't have to worry.

371
00:23:29,847 --> 00:23:31,724
This guy's a PNU.

372
00:23:32,975 --> 00:23:34,268
"PNU"?

373
00:23:34,352 --> 00:23:36,854
Yes, it's a term HR uses.

374
00:23:40,441 --> 00:23:42,193
It refers to someone who is useless.

375
00:23:42,568 --> 00:23:44,320
What? That's so mean.

376
00:23:44,987 --> 00:23:46,739
When a printed report has many pages

377
00:23:47,073 --> 00:23:50,535
you can fold the corner like this
so the big bosses can flip easily.

378
00:23:50,618 --> 00:23:52,078
Don't you think they'd appreciate it?

379
00:23:52,620 --> 00:23:53,746
You're so thoughtful.

380
00:23:55,832 --> 00:23:57,083
Are you serious?

381
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,252
- What?
- Never mind.

382
00:23:59,794 --> 00:24:01,587
This is how I became a team leader.

383
00:24:01,671 --> 00:24:03,130
Must be why I'm still a manager.

384
00:24:06,509 --> 00:24:08,010
I think it looks great.

385
00:24:13,933 --> 00:24:17,270
SEARCH HAEMU GROUP: JOO IN-A

386
00:24:17,770 --> 00:24:19,647
JOO IN-A'S PERSONNEL FILE

387
00:24:22,775 --> 00:24:23,776
SEARCH REQUEST FOR LEISURE STIPEND

388
00:24:23,860 --> 00:24:25,820
NO REQUEST FOR LEISURE STIPEND

389
00:24:27,530 --> 00:24:28,698
NO APPROVED REQUEST FOR LEAVE

390
00:24:28,781 --> 00:24:29,824
NO RECORD OF COMPANY CARD USE

391
00:24:43,838 --> 00:24:46,966
She doesn't go on leave
or claim any benefits.

392
00:24:47,049 --> 00:24:48,342
And she doesn't eat much.

393
00:24:49,969 --> 00:24:51,971
What does she live for?

394
00:24:56,767 --> 00:24:58,060
Did I get you?

395
00:24:58,144 --> 00:24:59,729
You almost fell onto your backside.

396
00:25:00,479 --> 00:25:01,731
Is this what gives her joy?

397
00:25:02,356 --> 00:25:03,441
I scored.

398
00:25:05,192 --> 00:25:08,362
Wait, were you the one
looking after this plant?

399
00:25:09,113 --> 00:25:10,281
Oh, yes.

400
00:25:10,364 --> 00:25:12,408
I water it whenever I think of it.

401
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:15,995
You're surprisingly thoughtful,
Mr. Noh.

402
00:25:16,621 --> 00:25:17,788
It's quite pretty.

403
00:25:20,333 --> 00:25:21,542
It smells, too.

404
00:25:33,471 --> 00:25:34,764
She's pretty.

405
00:25:35,389 --> 00:25:38,059
Well, I guess you can't say
she isn't pretty.

406
00:25:39,644 --> 00:25:40,645
What was that?

407
00:25:41,729 --> 00:25:43,606
I think you just smiled at me.

408
00:25:44,607 --> 00:25:45,816
That's because...

409
00:25:46,275 --> 00:25:48,903
Do I look funny to you, Mr. Noh?

410
00:25:48,986 --> 00:25:50,279
No, it's not that.

411
00:25:50,363 --> 00:25:52,281
I found your prank hilarious.

412
00:25:52,365 --> 00:25:53,616
When you jump-scared me.

413
00:25:54,408 --> 00:25:56,077
The more I think about it,
the funnier it is.

414
00:25:57,828 --> 00:26:00,247
The more I get to know you,
the more I see your humor.

415
00:26:03,042 --> 00:26:05,002
You caught on?

416
00:26:06,170 --> 00:26:07,880
I knew it. You have the wit.

417
00:26:08,422 --> 00:26:10,466
I don't get
why people are afraid of me.

418
00:26:10,549 --> 00:26:12,677
I'm hilarious, aren't I?

419
00:26:13,636 --> 00:26:14,762
You are.

420
00:26:14,845 --> 00:26:16,222
You get my wit.

421
00:26:19,475 --> 00:26:21,477
Oh, my gosh.

422
00:26:22,269 --> 00:26:25,648
My blood sugar must be going low.

423
00:26:26,899 --> 00:26:30,611
Where was Ms. Yoon's snack box?

424
00:26:32,446 --> 00:26:33,489
What's going on?

425
00:26:33,572 --> 00:26:36,367
Ms. Yoon,
The snack box is in here, right?

426
00:26:36,742 --> 00:26:37,868
Your box of snacks

427
00:26:38,411 --> 00:26:39,912
full of candies and chocolates.

428
00:26:40,371 --> 00:26:41,747
The drawer's locked.

429
00:26:43,165 --> 00:26:44,166
Ms. Yoon.

430
00:26:44,792 --> 00:26:47,044
Did you not like
my getting into your snack box?

431
00:26:47,878 --> 00:26:50,006
You should've told me so.

432
00:26:50,381 --> 00:26:53,676
Locking it away is harsh on your part
and embarrassing for me.

433
00:26:54,135 --> 00:26:55,928
I kept dropping hints
that I didn't like it.

434
00:26:56,679 --> 00:26:58,639
You failed to pick up on them.

435
00:27:00,016 --> 00:27:01,267
Oh, dear. I feel bad.

436
00:27:01,726 --> 00:27:03,144
- My gosh.
- What's wrong?

437
00:27:05,146 --> 00:27:07,732
Mr. Moo,
I think you need to see this.

438
00:27:10,818 --> 00:27:12,194
IF THEY DO THIS IN PUBLIC,
THEN IN PRIVATE...

439
00:27:12,278 --> 00:27:13,279
OH, MY GOSH! SPARE ME!

440
00:27:15,197 --> 00:27:18,117
Wow, you're the talk of the town.

441
00:27:22,872 --> 00:27:23,873
MADAM KILLER IS HILARIOUS

442
00:27:23,956 --> 00:27:26,000
"The Madam Killer"? Goodness.

443
00:27:26,083 --> 00:27:27,585
You're a killer, too, Mr. Moo?

444
00:27:27,668 --> 00:27:29,879
I had a nickname similar to that.

445
00:27:29,962 --> 00:27:31,422
It's not at all like that.

446
00:27:31,505 --> 00:27:33,966
Why would I go around killing ladies?

447
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:38,512
The photo was taken at an angle
that made us look suspicious.

448
00:27:38,846 --> 00:27:39,889
We were...

449
00:27:40,389 --> 00:27:43,309
That lady and I don't have
any kind of relationship.

450
00:27:44,435 --> 00:27:49,106
I can't believe that smoke
sometimes does appear without a fire.

451
00:27:49,315 --> 00:27:52,735
This isn't just some smoke.
The blaze could take us all down.

452
00:27:55,362 --> 00:27:56,489
Assistant Manager Ahn Min-su.

453
00:27:56,697 --> 00:27:57,990
Yes, Ms. Joo?

454
00:28:03,412 --> 00:28:05,623
I need you to look into this.

455
00:28:05,956 --> 00:28:08,167
Mr. Noh usually takes the PM cases

456
00:28:08,250 --> 00:28:10,169
but that would be inappropriate
as they're teammates.

457
00:28:10,586 --> 00:28:12,338
Pardon? Whose case am I taking on?

458
00:28:12,671 --> 00:28:14,131
Mr. Moo's case.

459
00:28:14,757 --> 00:28:15,758
- Gosh...
- Wait.

460
00:28:16,884 --> 00:28:18,385
Are you going to investigate this?

461
00:28:18,469 --> 00:28:19,678
Of course, I must.

462
00:28:19,762 --> 00:28:22,056
The case is big enough
that everyone's talking about it.

463
00:28:22,139 --> 00:28:24,683
Ms. Joo. It's just a random incident.

464
00:28:24,767 --> 00:28:26,185
It can't even be called a case.

465
00:28:26,268 --> 00:28:28,604
I'm innocent. You know what I'm like.

466
00:28:28,687 --> 00:28:29,772
Yes, Mr. Moo.

467
00:28:29,855 --> 00:28:32,108
That's all you have to say
when you're interviewed.

468
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:35,444
Drop everything you were working on
until the case is concluded.

469
00:28:35,778 --> 00:28:37,404
If anything needs to be approved...

470
00:28:38,114 --> 00:28:39,740
Manager Cha Sung-tae,
that's your duty now.

471
00:28:41,951 --> 00:28:42,952
That's all.

472
00:28:53,921 --> 00:28:55,965
Why are you still here?
You're dismissed.

473
00:28:57,049 --> 00:28:59,009
Oh, dear. It really isn't anything.

474
00:29:00,094 --> 00:29:01,554
It's really nothing.

475
00:29:03,097 --> 00:29:04,140
My goodness...

476
00:29:31,041 --> 00:29:33,043
WRITTEN STATEMENT

477
00:29:51,478 --> 00:29:52,938
I'm home.

478
00:29:57,359 --> 00:29:58,360
Is everyone in bed?

479
00:30:00,321 --> 00:30:01,363
Are the girls asleep?

480
00:30:07,036 --> 00:30:10,956
OUR AUDIT TEAM LEADER'S CHEATING

481
00:30:11,707 --> 00:30:13,167
They say this is you.

482
00:30:13,792 --> 00:30:14,793
Yes.

483
00:30:17,630 --> 00:30:18,756
The food

484
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:21,550
you brought me last night.

485
00:30:22,801 --> 00:30:24,053
Did she give it to you?

486
00:30:27,097 --> 00:30:29,475
- Did she?
- No, it's not like that.

487
00:30:31,227 --> 00:30:32,937
How should I explain?

488
00:30:44,406 --> 00:30:46,242
Based on how she treated Mr. Moo

489
00:30:46,575 --> 00:30:48,535
she wouldn't do anything.
wrong or immoral

490
00:30:52,206 --> 00:30:53,666
Am I wasting my time?

491
00:31:00,506 --> 00:31:02,258
Hang on. She's not going home?

492
00:31:03,175 --> 00:31:04,260
Darn it.

493
00:32:18,917 --> 00:32:20,961
Okay. This is it.

494
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:40,189
SEON DRAWING CLASS,
RECREATIONAL CLASS FOR ADULTS

495
00:32:40,272 --> 00:32:41,440
"Recreational art"?

496
00:32:45,361 --> 00:32:46,362
Excuse me.

497
00:32:47,237 --> 00:32:48,530
Are you going inside?

498
00:32:49,406 --> 00:32:51,033
No, sorry.

499
00:32:59,083 --> 00:33:01,085
Was drawing her hobby?

500
00:33:11,428 --> 00:33:13,472
- Hello.
- Morning.

501
00:33:17,309 --> 00:33:18,644
Oh, my goodness!

502
00:33:19,061 --> 00:33:20,437
Mr. Moo!

503
00:33:21,063 --> 00:33:22,481
Oh, dear. My bad.

504
00:33:22,773 --> 00:33:24,066
My gosh.

505
00:33:24,650 --> 00:33:25,692
Goodness me.

506
00:33:27,569 --> 00:33:29,488
Oh, dear.

507
00:33:37,579 --> 00:33:40,040
Did you spend the night here?

508
00:33:40,416 --> 00:33:42,209
Did you argue
with your wife last night?

509
00:33:42,292 --> 00:33:44,503
Why sleep here
when we have a night duty room?

510
00:33:44,586 --> 00:33:46,505
What are you doing here, Mr. Moo?

511
00:33:46,588 --> 00:33:48,006
Good morning, Ms. Joo.

512
00:33:48,215 --> 00:33:51,468
Something came up,
and I couldn't go home last night.

513
00:33:51,718 --> 00:33:54,054
I couldn't think
of anywhere else to go.

514
00:33:54,138 --> 00:33:56,056
So you decided to come to the office?

515
00:33:58,934 --> 00:34:01,603
You don't seem to know
where to draw the line.

516
00:34:02,229 --> 00:34:05,232
You take cafeteria food home
and come here to sleep at night.

517
00:34:09,194 --> 00:34:10,195
Please leave

518
00:34:10,946 --> 00:34:11,947
immediately.

519
00:34:12,489 --> 00:34:13,824
- Sorry?
- The subject of investigation

520
00:34:13,907 --> 00:34:16,493
does not have free access
to the office while it's ongoing.

521
00:34:17,035 --> 00:34:19,371
This was far too careless of you
as the head of an audit team.

522
00:34:20,414 --> 00:34:21,498
Ms. Pyun.

523
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:24,376
Request a restriction of his access
to General Affairs.

524
00:34:25,502 --> 00:34:28,505
- Do we have to go that far...
- Going that far is our ground rule.

525
00:34:30,174 --> 00:34:32,050
And Audit Teams are here
to strictly abide by the rules.

526
00:34:32,759 --> 00:34:33,802
Yes, of course.

527
00:34:34,261 --> 00:34:36,930
I should've thought this through.
I'll leave right away.

528
00:34:37,931 --> 00:34:39,141
Goodness, I'm sorry.

529
00:34:39,850 --> 00:34:41,351
Please let me just get my shoes.

530
00:34:42,394 --> 00:34:43,437
Sorry.

531
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:46,023
Ms. Pyun, here's my employee ID.

532
00:34:46,899 --> 00:34:48,525
Mr. Baek, can you put the box away?

533
00:34:49,151 --> 00:34:52,029
Goodness. I'm sorry. I apologize.

534
00:34:52,112 --> 00:34:54,281
I'm so sorry.

535
00:35:12,674 --> 00:35:14,092
Mister, you're Moo Kwang-il,
aren't you?

536
00:35:14,593 --> 00:35:16,678
- Yes, who are you?
- Don't you know me?

537
00:35:17,262 --> 00:35:18,972
We met at my grandfather's funeral.

538
00:35:20,849 --> 00:35:24,186
Yes, you're Ms. Eom's eldest son.
It's nice to see you.

539
00:35:26,021 --> 00:35:28,148
I should've known
when you were acting nosy.

540
00:35:28,982 --> 00:35:30,734
Work colleague, my foot.

541
00:35:31,276 --> 00:35:33,153
Who would care
about an outsourced worker's family?

542
00:35:33,237 --> 00:35:34,238
You were coming onto her!

543
00:35:35,364 --> 00:35:38,325
There must be
a huge misunderstanding.

544
00:35:38,408 --> 00:35:40,702
A misunderstanding?
That's easy for you to say.

545
00:35:41,203 --> 00:35:43,580
My mom lost her job
and can't make a living anymore!

546
00:35:43,956 --> 00:35:46,041
You'll probably be fine
because you're a big corporate guy

547
00:35:46,625 --> 00:35:48,627
but my mom is an expendable! Get it?

548
00:35:48,710 --> 00:35:50,128
Let go of me!

549
00:35:50,420 --> 00:35:51,922
- Sir.
- Goodness!

550
00:35:52,005 --> 00:35:53,840
Did she seem that easy to you,
you punk?

551
00:35:54,508 --> 00:35:56,552
- Hey, goodness. Wait a second.
- Let go of me!

552
00:35:57,010 --> 00:35:58,178
Let go!

553
00:35:58,262 --> 00:35:59,555
- You can't do this here.
- Let go!

554
00:36:00,931 --> 00:36:03,100
You went around acting nosy
like you were my dad. This is great.

555
00:36:03,183 --> 00:36:05,936
You can now be my dad
and make a living for me, okay?

556
00:36:06,019 --> 00:36:08,230
Dad... Father...

557
00:36:08,313 --> 00:36:09,356
- Sir.
- Darn it.

558
00:36:12,609 --> 00:36:14,444
Will you let go of me?

559
00:36:14,695 --> 00:36:16,196
Just let go!

560
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:17,656
Please calm down.

561
00:36:18,532 --> 00:36:19,575
Let go of me!

562
00:36:20,325 --> 00:36:22,411
How dare you hit on my poor mother?

563
00:36:22,494 --> 00:36:24,788
How can you be so vulgar
at your age? Darn it!

564
00:36:24,871 --> 00:36:27,249
I knew he was like that
when he acted too nice.

565
00:36:46,643 --> 00:36:49,229
It was a temporary reaction
due to stress

566
00:36:49,313 --> 00:36:50,856
so please get a good rest.

567
00:36:51,648 --> 00:36:54,067
Would you like anything to eat?

568
00:37:01,241 --> 00:37:02,868
Come on, let's leave.
Get a good rest.

569
00:37:05,412 --> 00:37:07,706
I've never seen Mr. Moo
look so disheartened before.

570
00:37:07,956 --> 00:37:09,791
He must feel awful.

571
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:13,462
People took his act of kindness
and called it an affair and whatnot.

572
00:37:13,545 --> 00:37:15,631
They all blamed him
like they were hunting him down.

573
00:37:15,714 --> 00:37:17,382
It is too petty a matter
to even make excuses for.

574
00:37:17,799 --> 00:37:19,635
Jeez, this is awful.

575
00:37:20,385 --> 00:37:22,220
The bulletin has become crazier
in the meantime.

576
00:37:22,971 --> 00:37:25,223
"No one is kind enough to visit
the cafeteria lady's dad's funeral."

577
00:37:25,515 --> 00:37:26,808
They say it's 100 percent an affair.

578
00:37:26,892 --> 00:37:28,769
Man, that's just too much.

579
00:37:29,144 --> 00:37:31,146
Why are people like this? Why?

580
00:37:32,606 --> 00:37:33,815
- Hello.
- Hello.

581
00:37:33,899 --> 00:37:35,609
Is Mr. Moo inside?

582
00:37:36,485 --> 00:37:39,071
- Is he all right?
- What do you think?

583
00:37:39,655 --> 00:37:41,365
- Do you have the result?
- Yes.

584
00:37:41,448 --> 00:37:43,325
It doesn't seem like
they were having an affair

585
00:37:44,159 --> 00:37:46,495
but Mr. Moo will be reprimanded...

586
00:37:46,578 --> 00:37:48,455
If he didn't have an affair,
why should he be?

587
00:37:48,538 --> 00:37:50,374
After all, there was a commotion
within the company

588
00:37:50,457 --> 00:37:52,834
and our reputation fell
when the word got out, so...

589
00:37:52,918 --> 00:37:54,753
How is that his fault?

590
00:37:54,836 --> 00:37:57,464
- He's the victim of a witch hunt!
- Yes.

591
00:37:57,547 --> 00:38:00,384
I agree with you, but it's Ms. Joo.

592
00:38:01,301 --> 00:38:02,969
- Excuse me.
- Wait a second.

593
00:38:03,470 --> 00:38:05,472
Mr. Moo can't afford
to be shocked anymore right now.

594
00:38:06,223 --> 00:38:07,307
Also, we cannot accept

595
00:38:07,933 --> 00:38:09,518
this disciplinary action.

596
00:38:10,102 --> 00:38:11,770
How will that change anything?

597
00:38:12,270 --> 00:38:15,524
Let's go and ask Ms. Joo
to withdraw this as a team.

598
00:38:16,942 --> 00:38:18,944
Yes, it's time to protest.

599
00:38:20,946 --> 00:38:23,740
Well, the thing is...
It's embarrassing to bring this up.

600
00:38:24,491 --> 00:38:27,619
I lost my fortune in crypto before
and couldn't pay my credit card bill

601
00:38:27,703 --> 00:38:28,745
but Mr. Moo helped me out.

602
00:38:29,162 --> 00:38:33,166
And she should do her part as a boss
to cover for her team in these times.

603
00:38:33,250 --> 00:38:35,669
I wonder if she'd do that
when I do something wrong

604
00:38:35,752 --> 00:38:37,504
- so it feels very personal.
- You're right.

605
00:38:38,046 --> 00:38:39,506
This isn't just Mr. Moo's business.

606
00:38:39,589 --> 00:38:41,466
This is everyone's problem.

607
00:38:41,550 --> 00:38:44,970
Things seem
a bit heated up right now.

608
00:38:45,345 --> 00:38:47,264
Why don't we calm down
and use our common sense to think...

609
00:38:47,347 --> 00:38:49,015
Do you want to stay out of this?

610
00:38:49,891 --> 00:38:53,437
Why? Do you not want to take part
because you're the Audit Team's ace?

611
00:39:04,781 --> 00:39:06,783
COME TO THE ROOFTOP! PLEASE
FROM AUDIT TEAM 3

612
00:39:50,869 --> 00:39:52,329
It was a phrase
I haven't heard for a while.

613
00:39:52,412 --> 00:39:53,830
"Come to the rooftop."

614
00:39:55,332 --> 00:39:56,708
So are you ganging up on me?

615
00:39:57,501 --> 00:39:58,919
It's kind of cheap
to outnumber me like this.

616
00:39:59,252 --> 00:40:00,462
Why don't a few of you cross over?

617
00:40:06,968 --> 00:40:07,969
Ms. Joo.

618
00:40:08,845 --> 00:40:11,097
We would like to speak to you
as a team

619
00:40:11,598 --> 00:40:13,517
regarding Mr. Moo.

620
00:40:16,061 --> 00:40:18,730
Withdraw the disciplinary action
against him, please.

621
00:40:19,231 --> 00:40:20,398
- Please do that!
- Please do that!

622
00:40:21,358 --> 00:40:24,027
He's already suffering
from all kinds of malicious rumors.

623
00:40:24,110 --> 00:40:27,697
The notice of his disciplinary action
will only make matters worse.

624
00:40:28,073 --> 00:40:30,700
He wasn't at fault to begin with.
It was a misunderstanding.

625
00:41:07,028 --> 00:41:08,196
Oh, my gosh!

626
00:41:17,289 --> 00:41:18,415
Never mind.

627
00:41:19,624 --> 00:41:20,876
My legs were hurting.

628
00:41:26,798 --> 00:41:28,508
Now, where were we?

629
00:41:28,592 --> 00:41:31,219
Yes, that Mr. Moo
didn't do anything wrong.

630
00:41:33,889 --> 00:41:36,057
You're right.
There was no infidelity between them.

631
00:41:37,058 --> 00:41:40,395
But he took cafeteria food out,
which is considered company property

632
00:41:40,478 --> 00:41:42,105
and exchanged
a considerable amount of money

633
00:41:42,188 --> 00:41:43,315
with an outsourced staff member

634
00:41:43,648 --> 00:41:45,567
causing a controversy
inside and outside the office.

635
00:41:46,610 --> 00:41:47,694
I think

636
00:41:48,278 --> 00:41:49,779
reprimanding him sounds adequate.

637
00:41:50,906 --> 00:41:53,158
Will anyone care
about the whole story?

638
00:41:54,117 --> 00:41:57,370
They'll brand him for infidelity,
thinking the suspicions are right

639
00:41:57,871 --> 00:41:59,289
because of the disciplinary action.

640
00:42:02,792 --> 00:42:05,712
Then will glossing over this matter
put everything to its rest?

641
00:42:06,671 --> 00:42:08,715
"The Audit Team nitpicks over
every little detail with us

642
00:42:08,798 --> 00:42:10,008
but they cover for their own."

643
00:42:11,051 --> 00:42:12,844
Wouldn't people insult
the entire team?

644
00:42:12,928 --> 00:42:15,639
You're our boss
before you're the Head of Audit.

645
00:42:16,139 --> 00:42:18,558
And shouldn't you draw the line
and protect us in times like these

646
00:42:18,642 --> 00:42:20,185
if you truly are our boss?

647
00:42:20,769 --> 00:42:23,730
How can we have faith in this company
if you treat us like this?

648
00:42:30,946 --> 00:42:33,823
You don't need to have faith to work.
We aren't a church.

649
00:42:35,325 --> 00:42:38,078
You come to work
because you get paid to be here!

650
00:42:38,787 --> 00:42:41,081
And because we are paid,
I will fulfill my responsibility

651
00:42:41,164 --> 00:42:43,291
and Mr. Moo must fulfill his own.

652
00:42:49,381 --> 00:42:50,423
"Draw the line"?

653
00:42:52,008 --> 00:42:54,552
That line is there
because you are not to step over it.

654
00:43:08,316 --> 00:43:10,485
White Blood Cell, you're something.

655
00:43:10,568 --> 00:43:12,529
Never mind. Go ahead.

656
00:43:13,947 --> 00:43:15,573
I think we stepped off the deep end.

657
00:43:19,119 --> 00:43:20,662
We can't end it like this.

658
00:43:21,496 --> 00:43:23,123
The negotiation is off

659
00:43:24,124 --> 00:43:25,625
so we must act as a group.

660
00:43:25,709 --> 00:43:28,128
There's no talking to her,
so we must show her with our action.

661
00:43:43,977 --> 00:43:45,270
Excuse me.

662
00:43:46,187 --> 00:43:49,399
Ms. Joo, the entire team
took the rest of the day off.

663
00:43:49,941 --> 00:43:52,652
They called it a kind of a strike.

664
00:43:53,945 --> 00:43:55,864
They want you to retract
Mr. Moo's disciplinary action.

665
00:44:01,828 --> 00:44:04,706
Goodness. There's a fly in here.
It's a dung fly.

666
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:08,960
Is the office not tidy enough?

667
00:44:12,047 --> 00:44:13,048
Sorry?

668
00:44:14,716 --> 00:44:15,759
Yes.

669
00:44:17,218 --> 00:44:18,428
That was it?

670
00:44:19,471 --> 00:44:21,014
All right. Bye.

671
00:44:22,766 --> 00:44:23,933
Why? What did Ms. Joo say?

672
00:44:26,561 --> 00:44:27,771
Nothing.

673
00:44:29,773 --> 00:44:31,024
She caught a fly and turned around.

674
00:44:31,107 --> 00:44:32,400
- That's it?
- Yes.

675
00:44:32,484 --> 00:44:34,110
She must think we're a huge joke.

676
00:44:34,194 --> 00:44:36,404
How can she not respond in any way
even after our group strike?

677
00:44:36,488 --> 00:44:37,989
That's why she's Joo In-a.

678
00:44:38,073 --> 00:44:40,241
I expected this, but how could she
not be bothered at all?

679
00:44:40,325 --> 00:44:41,326
Whatever. Let's keep it going.

680
00:44:41,409 --> 00:44:42,827
Take tomorrow off, too.

681
00:44:42,911 --> 00:44:43,912
Wait a minute.

682
00:44:44,746 --> 00:44:46,748
If Ms. Joo doesn't approve
our leave request

683
00:44:46,831 --> 00:44:48,458
it'll be considered
unauthorized absence.

684
00:44:49,959 --> 00:44:51,169
Wait, in that case...

685
00:44:51,503 --> 00:44:54,339
Is there a possibility
that we'll also get punishment?

686
00:44:54,756 --> 00:44:58,259
Come on.
Ms. Joo can't be that inconsiderate.

687
00:44:58,343 --> 00:45:00,178
Isn't that why we're here now?

688
00:45:05,058 --> 00:45:06,101
In that case

689
00:45:06,726 --> 00:45:09,479
why don't one of us go upstairs
and do a quick vibe check?

690
00:45:09,562 --> 00:45:11,439
And check how Ms. Joo is doing.

691
00:45:12,482 --> 00:45:13,775
Do you want to go, Mr. Noh?

692
00:45:14,150 --> 00:45:15,151
Me?

693
00:45:15,235 --> 00:45:18,446
DOES ANYBODY KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE MADAM KILLER?

694
00:45:19,155 --> 00:45:20,156
Lastly

695
00:45:20,532 --> 00:45:23,118
Managing Director Jeon Sung-yeol
will return to the headquarters.

696
00:45:24,202 --> 00:45:25,662
I expect you to show him support.

697
00:45:36,422 --> 00:45:38,091
Now it's official.

698
00:45:38,174 --> 00:45:39,592
It must be what the president wants.

699
00:45:39,676 --> 00:45:40,802
Of course, it is.

700
00:45:40,885 --> 00:45:43,054
Jeez, there are two suns
radiating up in our sky.

701
00:45:50,019 --> 00:45:51,104
It'll happen, anyway.

702
00:45:57,694 --> 00:45:58,778
Ms. Boo.

703
00:46:03,449 --> 00:46:04,492
It's Se-young.

704
00:46:06,911 --> 00:46:07,996
Se-young.

705
00:46:09,747 --> 00:46:12,041
Isn't it about time
that you took a measure for Mr. Moo?

706
00:46:12,667 --> 00:46:15,170
HR and Information Office
is in charge of the intranet.

707
00:46:16,087 --> 00:46:18,006
I already shared the result
of our investigation

708
00:46:18,089 --> 00:46:19,632
that the infidelity was groundless.

709
00:46:20,717 --> 00:46:22,010
But the bulletin
is still going strong.

710
00:46:22,093 --> 00:46:23,553
People are like that.

711
00:46:24,262 --> 00:46:26,097
No one cares about the truth.

712
00:46:26,181 --> 00:46:27,265
Exactly.

713
00:46:27,891 --> 00:46:30,310
So I'm asking HR
to delete those posts accordingly.

714
00:46:33,313 --> 00:46:34,856
We've been a little busy.

715
00:46:35,982 --> 00:46:37,066
I'll look into it, though.

716
00:46:38,318 --> 00:46:39,861
It's because of Mr. Jeon, isn't it?

717
00:46:42,655 --> 00:46:44,365
The bulletin always has
posts about him

718
00:46:44,449 --> 00:46:46,284
so you're diverting people
and manipulating opinions.

719
00:46:47,410 --> 00:46:49,204
I've noticed it a while ago

720
00:46:49,287 --> 00:46:50,788
but HR was doing what HR does

721
00:46:51,247 --> 00:46:52,707
so I was going to observe.

722
00:46:53,499 --> 00:46:54,542
But you know

723
00:46:55,793 --> 00:46:57,629
I've had enough of your nonsense.

724
00:46:58,004 --> 00:46:59,047
Nonsense?

725
00:46:59,797 --> 00:47:02,759
Hey. Do you think HR is a joke?

726
00:47:06,763 --> 00:47:07,805
Anyway.

727
00:47:08,389 --> 00:47:10,433
But in the end,
I guess I have to thank him.

728
00:47:11,142 --> 00:47:13,519
You always cover up a rumor
with another rumor.

729
00:47:15,647 --> 00:47:16,689
Right?

730
00:47:17,607 --> 00:47:20,276
You cover up a rumor
with another rumor, right?

731
00:47:28,743 --> 00:47:31,746
What are you doing?
Hey. Let go of me. Hey!

732
00:47:31,829 --> 00:47:32,914
You!

733
00:47:33,414 --> 00:47:36,251
Have you lost your mind?
Get over here.

734
00:47:36,668 --> 00:47:38,711
Let go of me!

735
00:47:38,795 --> 00:47:40,880
Let go! Hey!

736
00:47:41,464 --> 00:47:44,425
Let go! Let go of my hair!

737
00:47:44,509 --> 00:47:46,552
Have you lost your mind?

738
00:47:46,636 --> 00:47:48,554
Hey! Let go of me!

739
00:47:53,101 --> 00:47:55,353
Let go of my hair!

740
00:47:55,436 --> 00:47:56,938
'22 RECRUITS GROUP CHAT
1 NEW MESSAGE

741
00:47:57,021 --> 00:47:59,107
AUDIT TEAM 3 GROUP CHAT
1 NEW MESSAGE

742
00:48:00,316 --> 00:48:02,151
You. Let go of me.

743
00:48:02,485 --> 00:48:03,736
Let go!

744
00:48:21,129 --> 00:48:22,171
What kind of person

745
00:48:22,880 --> 00:48:24,424
is Joo In-a?

746
00:48:30,763 --> 00:48:32,307
- No way.
- This is the craziest ever.

747
00:48:32,390 --> 00:48:34,767
- People made so many clips.
- Why did they fight?

748
00:48:34,851 --> 00:48:35,935
They've always been enemies.

749
00:48:36,644 --> 00:48:37,687
Everyone knew.

750
00:48:39,981 --> 00:48:42,191
In the end, did everything go
according to her plan?

751
00:48:42,734 --> 00:48:43,776
Right?

752
00:48:43,985 --> 00:48:46,487
You cover up a rumor
with another rumor, right?

753
00:48:58,374 --> 00:48:59,459
Know your limits.

754
00:48:59,751 --> 00:49:02,295
A cornered mouse can bite the cat.

755
00:49:14,265 --> 00:49:15,308
Ms. Joo.

756
00:49:15,850 --> 00:49:17,060
I need to talk to you.

757
00:49:19,354 --> 00:49:21,481
Unfortunately, I'm done for the day.

758
00:49:22,023 --> 00:49:23,524
Please come to my office tomorrow.

759
00:49:25,026 --> 00:49:26,194
What the heck is this complaint?

760
00:49:26,277 --> 00:49:28,237
Wasn't the disciplinary action
more than enough?

761
00:49:28,696 --> 00:49:30,365
Are you trying

762
00:49:30,865 --> 00:49:33,076
to end someone's life?

763
00:49:34,285 --> 00:49:35,411
Let's talk.

764
00:50:08,528 --> 00:50:09,570
Anyway, Ms. Joo.

765
00:50:11,114 --> 00:50:12,407
Do you have to keep

766
00:50:13,699 --> 00:50:15,243
the rest of your fingers folded in?

767
00:50:18,955 --> 00:50:20,248
I wanted to make it easier for you.

768
00:50:22,208 --> 00:50:23,251
Right.

769
00:50:24,710 --> 00:50:26,796
Goodness. Of all those fingers,
you hurt this one.

770
00:50:36,639 --> 00:50:37,682
All done.

771
00:50:38,474 --> 00:50:41,185
I only gave you first aid,
so please see a doctor tomorrow.

772
00:50:41,269 --> 00:50:43,896
Okay. You're my savior today, so...

773
00:50:45,523 --> 00:50:47,400
Please enjoy, sir.

774
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:54,073
Is this what your life is worth?

775
00:50:54,157 --> 00:50:55,950
It's not for my life.
It's for my finger.

776
00:50:57,452 --> 00:50:59,162
I look stylish and powerful.

777
00:50:59,662 --> 00:51:00,705
I like this one.

778
00:51:01,664 --> 00:51:02,748
"This one"?

779
00:51:03,166 --> 00:51:04,500
Does this happen to you often?

780
00:51:04,584 --> 00:51:06,085
This is kind of cute, actually.

781
00:51:06,919 --> 00:51:08,921
Back in the day,
someone destroyed my computer

782
00:51:09,005 --> 00:51:11,507
and another employee fled after
splashing my seat with superglue.

783
00:51:11,841 --> 00:51:14,010
And a CEO of a corrupt business
struck my head with a golf club.

784
00:51:14,510 --> 00:51:15,595
I probably have a scar here.

785
00:51:15,678 --> 00:51:17,722
Right here. Can you see it?

786
00:51:18,222 --> 00:51:19,307
It's from my surgery back then.

787
00:51:19,974 --> 00:51:21,225
While I was working abroad

788
00:51:21,309 --> 00:51:23,478
the local gang
even threatened me with a knife.

789
00:51:24,520 --> 00:51:25,605
So I

790
00:51:26,564 --> 00:51:27,648
picked up a gun.

791
00:51:33,029 --> 00:51:34,489
That's why you're Joo-niper.

792
00:51:35,281 --> 00:51:37,742
So that rumor was true?
Did you really shoot a person?

793
00:51:38,367 --> 00:51:39,494
What do you think?

794
00:51:42,955 --> 00:51:44,207
No, I don't want to know.

795
00:51:54,258 --> 00:51:55,301
Ms. Joo.

796
00:51:57,011 --> 00:51:58,971
About your fight with the Head of HR.

797
00:52:04,769 --> 00:52:05,811
No, never mind.

798
00:52:12,318 --> 00:52:13,528
Are you perverted?

799
00:52:14,195 --> 00:52:16,656
- What?
- Do you get off on getting hated?

800
00:52:17,198 --> 00:52:19,408
I know it's hard not to make enemies
when you're working

801
00:52:19,492 --> 00:52:20,952
but you can try to make less.

802
00:52:21,661 --> 00:52:22,954
But it seems like

803
00:52:23,955 --> 00:52:25,623
you want to get hated

804
00:52:25,957 --> 00:52:27,083
even more than you actually want.

805
00:52:29,585 --> 00:52:31,504
No one wants to be hated.

806
00:52:32,296 --> 00:52:35,091
However, there are times
when I must position myself.

807
00:52:35,716 --> 00:52:37,760
I must either be a saint
or a villain.

808
00:52:38,594 --> 00:52:40,179
If I stay in the middle,
I get no work done

809
00:52:40,263 --> 00:52:42,473
lose my popularity,
and nothing works out.

810
00:52:43,599 --> 00:52:45,226
Do you know who your worst boss is?

811
00:52:47,019 --> 00:52:48,104
A non-committal jerk.

812
00:52:50,356 --> 00:52:51,399
Yes.

813
00:52:51,649 --> 00:52:53,317
You definitely are committed to one.

814
00:53:02,577 --> 00:53:03,744
But it must be lonely

815
00:53:05,580 --> 00:53:06,914
to have your sincerity misunderstood.

816
00:53:12,044 --> 00:53:13,379
Did you misunderstand me?

817
00:53:13,921 --> 00:53:14,964
How so?

818
00:53:18,634 --> 00:53:20,136
That you were a cold-hearted person

819
00:53:20,219 --> 00:53:23,931
who don't care about others' feelings
to accomplish your goals.

820
00:53:26,517 --> 00:53:27,685
Well, I thought so.

821
00:53:29,770 --> 00:53:31,814
But you seem to be someone
who does things your own way

822
00:53:32,982 --> 00:53:34,817
when you do something
you believe is right.

823
00:53:37,570 --> 00:53:39,822
People may misunderstand you
because of that

824
00:53:40,615 --> 00:53:42,241
and you put yourself
in a hard position

825
00:53:42,908 --> 00:53:44,035
but you do not back out

826
00:53:44,785 --> 00:53:45,870
or make excuses.

827
00:53:48,080 --> 00:53:49,332
I doubt it's easy

828
00:53:51,334 --> 00:53:52,460
to always live like that.

829
00:54:01,510 --> 00:54:02,553
Wow.

830
00:54:03,220 --> 00:54:04,805
You know how to talk, Mr. Noh.

831
00:54:05,765 --> 00:54:07,141
I was a bit moved just now.

832
00:54:10,436 --> 00:54:13,481
Anyway, don't you think
the misunderstanding was harsh?

833
00:54:13,898 --> 00:54:15,483
You practically thought
I was a psychopath.

834
00:54:15,566 --> 00:54:17,193
You do come across that way.

835
00:54:17,777 --> 00:54:18,944
Me?

836
00:54:19,028 --> 00:54:20,696
But I love people.

837
00:54:20,988 --> 00:54:22,531
Even personality tests say
I'm an extrovert

838
00:54:22,615 --> 00:54:24,367
- like a cute little puppy.
- Cute little puppy?

839
00:54:24,867 --> 00:54:27,495
People are intimidated by you!

840
00:54:30,414 --> 00:54:31,499
You can't have this.

841
00:54:32,500 --> 00:54:34,293
Look at this.

842
00:54:34,377 --> 00:54:36,337
This is why you come off like that.

843
00:54:36,921 --> 00:54:38,255
Give it back.

844
00:54:38,839 --> 00:54:41,300
I'm a big psychopath,
so I can't do that.

845
00:54:45,596 --> 00:54:47,390
It's even better
because I took it back from you.

846
00:54:48,224 --> 00:54:49,433
Don't finish it. It's mine...

847
00:54:59,068 --> 00:55:00,903
You skipped dinner today.

848
00:55:01,612 --> 00:55:02,988
You should eat,
even if you don't want to.

849
00:55:03,406 --> 00:55:05,116
Okay. Leave it there and go.

850
00:55:12,456 --> 00:55:13,958
It's the key to the studio apartment.

851
00:55:15,334 --> 00:55:16,877
Thank you for everything.

852
00:55:18,212 --> 00:55:19,505
While moving out

853
00:55:19,755 --> 00:55:22,299
I stole a bottle of your hard liquor
as a souvenir.

854
00:55:23,259 --> 00:55:24,260
Is that okay?

855
00:55:27,888 --> 00:55:29,181
I don't mind.

856
00:55:30,766 --> 00:55:31,809
But why the sudden change?

857
00:55:32,685 --> 00:55:34,895
Has your family matter been resolved?

858
00:55:35,312 --> 00:55:36,397
No.

859
00:55:37,148 --> 00:55:38,149
I just

860
00:55:40,192 --> 00:55:42,027
don't want to stay there anymore.

861
00:55:44,447 --> 00:55:45,781
Then where are you staying?

862
00:55:46,991 --> 00:55:49,034
- Is it safe?
- I'm not telling.

863
00:55:50,661 --> 00:55:52,913
I want you to be concerned

864
00:55:54,039 --> 00:55:55,082
about me.

865
00:56:26,030 --> 00:56:27,406
He wrapped it up so neatly.

866
00:57:31,011 --> 00:57:32,012
Jae-yeol!

867
00:57:52,408 --> 00:57:53,576
I'll see you more often now.

868
00:57:54,159 --> 00:57:55,202
Jae-yeol.

869
00:57:56,537 --> 00:57:57,580
Sure.

870
00:58:02,877 --> 00:58:04,670
It's been a while
since I've written an apology

871
00:58:04,753 --> 00:58:06,255
and I found the fun in it.

872
00:58:12,970 --> 00:58:14,763
- Mr. Moo.
- Yes?

873
00:58:14,847 --> 00:58:16,557
You're a special man who have worked

874
00:58:16,640 --> 00:58:18,934
in 12 teams, 5 branches,
and 3 different subsidiaries.

875
00:58:19,935 --> 00:58:21,854
You're highly interested
in every aspect of the company

876
00:58:21,937 --> 00:58:23,439
so you have information and network.

877
00:58:24,481 --> 00:58:26,567
It makes you a perfect candidate
to take up Audit Team Three

878
00:58:26,650 --> 00:58:28,444
a team that receives
dozens of complains a day.

879
00:58:29,403 --> 00:58:30,404
Above all

880
00:58:30,779 --> 00:58:32,615
you're a good leader
to your team members

881
00:58:32,865 --> 00:58:34,742
who each have a big personality.

882
00:58:35,034 --> 00:58:38,537
Goodness, I appreciate
your words of consolation.

883
00:58:38,621 --> 00:58:39,622
However

884
00:58:40,581 --> 00:58:41,749
that's a double-edged sword.

885
00:58:42,333 --> 00:58:44,168
Your sound personality

886
00:58:44,251 --> 00:58:46,545
sometimes doesn't fit
to be the leader of the Audit Team.

887
00:58:47,338 --> 00:58:49,673
Members of other departments are
the subjects of our investigation.

888
00:58:50,424 --> 00:58:51,926
Make use of them as your intel

889
00:58:52,009 --> 00:58:54,053
but please try to keep them
in a proper distance.

890
00:58:56,847 --> 00:58:58,974
How can I make use of people
as my intel?

891
00:58:59,058 --> 00:59:00,142
I'm not a spy.

892
00:59:01,852 --> 00:59:02,895
Goodness.

893
00:59:03,687 --> 00:59:04,730
Well, Ms. Joo.

894
00:59:05,230 --> 00:59:07,024
I crunched some numbers

895
00:59:08,150 --> 00:59:11,028
and realized that during weekdays,
I can only play with my daughters

896
00:59:11,111 --> 00:59:12,655
two hours a day at most.

897
00:59:13,322 --> 00:59:15,824
But I must sit here
and work with my colleagues

898
00:59:15,908 --> 00:59:17,910
for nine hours a day.

899
00:59:18,702 --> 00:59:19,912
And in those hours

900
00:59:20,162 --> 00:59:21,956
if I do not keep
a friendly relationship

901
00:59:22,247 --> 00:59:23,874
with my colleagues

902
00:59:24,541 --> 00:59:25,876
it would make my life

903
00:59:27,753 --> 00:59:29,088
too meaningless.

904
00:59:30,130 --> 00:59:31,131
In the future

905
00:59:31,715 --> 00:59:35,010
I will do my best to help out
if I find another colleague in need

906
00:59:35,552 --> 00:59:38,847
and gladly take any food they bring
if they decide to do that.

907
00:59:39,473 --> 00:59:41,141
I'll write up another apology
when that happens.

908
00:59:43,727 --> 00:59:44,770
I'm sorry.

909
00:59:46,063 --> 00:59:49,066
Anyway, I will do my job
without a big ambition

910
00:59:49,441 --> 00:59:52,569
but for a long time
while enjoying my time here.

911
00:59:59,326 --> 01:00:02,037
If you have nothing more to say,
then please excuse me.

912
01:00:03,414 --> 01:00:04,456
All right.

913
01:00:07,459 --> 01:00:08,669
Oh, Ms. Joo.

914
01:00:11,213 --> 01:00:14,967
By any chance,
did you pull out Ms. Boo's hair

915
01:00:15,759 --> 01:00:17,636
for my sake?

916
01:00:18,971 --> 01:00:20,264
Is that important?

917
01:00:21,306 --> 01:00:23,434
No. Please excuse me.

918
01:00:32,484 --> 01:00:33,527
Perhaps

919
01:00:34,611 --> 01:00:36,905
distinguishing between
your friend and foe at work

920
01:00:43,120 --> 01:00:45,039
is not that important.

921
01:00:49,543 --> 01:00:50,669
I don't work here anymore.

922
01:00:51,920 --> 01:00:54,173
I got a better job elsewhere,
so don't worry about me.

923
01:00:54,465 --> 01:00:56,341
Goodness,
you're such a talented person.

924
01:00:56,425 --> 01:00:57,468
Good for you.

925
01:00:59,428 --> 01:01:02,097
Please give me a call
when your twins get married.

926
01:01:02,556 --> 01:01:04,058
I may not give you as much

927
01:01:04,141 --> 01:01:05,642
but I want to show you
my token of sincerity.

928
01:01:05,726 --> 01:01:06,769
Of course.

929
01:01:11,356 --> 01:01:12,733
- Stay healthy.
- Thank you.

930
01:01:13,108 --> 01:01:14,276
Thank you for your hard work.

931
01:01:20,324 --> 01:01:21,700
What's more important is...

932
01:01:22,868 --> 01:01:26,872
HEAD OF AUDIT

933
01:01:26,955 --> 01:01:29,374
Gosh, the air in this office
is way too dry.

934
01:01:29,458 --> 01:01:31,418
I should tidy this up a little.

935
01:01:33,670 --> 01:01:35,631
Are you done?
Ms. Joo, here's your coffee.

936
01:01:36,048 --> 01:01:37,216
Goodness.

937
01:01:40,677 --> 01:01:42,012
Let me dry that off.

938
01:01:48,477 --> 01:01:51,021
Shoo!

939
01:01:52,940 --> 01:01:54,900
Shoo.

940
01:01:57,069 --> 01:01:58,153
Excuse us.

941
01:02:01,824 --> 01:02:03,909
...the discretion
not to turn your friend into a foe.

942
01:02:04,910 --> 01:02:06,495
By any chance, do you feel hot?

943
01:02:06,578 --> 01:02:07,913
Should I fan you?

944
01:02:07,996 --> 01:02:09,540
- Stronger.
- Stronger wind.

945
01:02:10,791 --> 01:02:11,917
Does that feel better?

946
01:02:23,679 --> 01:02:26,473
And the determination to gladly
become my colleague's friend.

947
01:02:27,891 --> 01:02:29,101
Perhaps those are more important.

948
01:02:47,327 --> 01:02:48,620
RECREATIONAL ART CLASS
TONIGHT AT 9 P.M.

949
01:02:52,541 --> 01:02:55,294
Even someone who has
a great reputation like Mr. Moo

950
01:02:56,170 --> 01:02:58,255
got cornered
because of a single photo.

951
01:03:00,299 --> 01:03:01,800
Joo In-a has enemies all around her.

952
01:03:06,346 --> 01:03:07,389
That report.

953
01:03:07,598 --> 01:03:09,141
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

954
01:03:09,224 --> 01:03:10,601
It's probably
an attempt to entrap her.

955
01:03:11,643 --> 01:03:13,729
All right. I need to stop here.

956
01:03:48,138 --> 01:03:49,348
Wait. Excuse me.

957
01:03:51,016 --> 01:03:52,976
Do you need that
to take a class here?

958
01:03:53,227 --> 01:03:54,561
Oh, yes.

959
01:03:55,354 --> 01:03:57,731
The club members must bring it.

960
01:03:57,981 --> 01:03:59,942
I see. Thank you.

961
01:04:07,824 --> 01:04:08,867
What's going on?

962
01:04:09,826 --> 01:04:11,286
She wasn't carrying that thing.

963
01:06:12,741 --> 01:06:15,660
FILING FOR LOVE

964
01:06:16,119 --> 01:06:19,039
GUEST APPEARANCE BY LEE JUNG-EUN

965
01:06:44,689 --> 01:06:45,816
How can I act like nothing happened?

966
01:06:45,899 --> 01:06:46,900
It's just not the same.

967
01:06:48,110 --> 01:06:49,277
This is driving me crazy.

968
01:06:49,361 --> 01:06:51,822
Babe, come here. Hurry.

969
01:06:52,447 --> 01:06:53,740
- Bravo!
- There's

970
01:06:53,824 --> 01:06:55,325
definitely more to this incident.

971
01:06:55,409 --> 01:06:58,036
Who did you mess with

972
01:06:58,120 --> 01:06:59,287
to become their target?

973
01:06:59,371 --> 01:07:00,872
If this backfires
due to a careless move

974
01:07:00,956 --> 01:07:02,165
you could be in serious trouble.

975
01:07:02,249 --> 01:07:03,375
I'll make sure it doesn't backfire.

976
01:07:03,458 --> 01:07:04,584
Room 1306, please.

977
01:07:04,668 --> 01:07:06,002
I'm staying the night.

978
01:07:06,086 --> 01:07:08,588
Why are you hesitating now?
You've already seen it.

979
01:07:09,965 --> 01:07:11,925
- Could you stop staring at my body?
- Sorry?

980
01:07:25,814 --> 01:07:27,816
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
